17. Bh4 Be7 18. Bg5 Nd5 19. Bd2 Bf6 20. c4 {Bilguun,S (2269)-Segarra,R (2343)
Manila 2013 0-1 (50)}) 6. d4 $146 {Black's piece can't move: f8} (6. d3 Bg4 7.
O-O e6 8. Bg5 Be7 9. Bh4 O-O 10. Bg3 Qd7 11. Ne5 Nxe5 12. Bxe5 Bxe2 13. Qxe2 c6
14. Qf3 Nd5 15. Nxd5 cxd5 16. c4 Rfd8 17. Rac1 Bf8 18. Qg3 Rac8 19. Bf6 Re8 20.
b3 Rc6 {Marinsek,T (2195)-Nikolov,S (2415) Pula 1998 1/2-1/2 (103)}) (6. Nb5
Qd8 7. d4 a6 8. Nc3 Bf5 9. Bf4 e6 10. O-O Be7 11. h3 O-O 12. Re1 Nb4 13. Rc1 c5
14. Be3 Qc7 15. a3 Nbd5 16. Nxd5 Nxd5 17. Bd3 Bg6 18. Bxg6 hxg6 19. c4 Nxe3 20.
fxe3 Bf6 {Kosanski,S (2365)-Nikolov,S (2415) Radenci 1998 1-0 (60)}) 6... Bf5 (
6... a6 7. a3 $14) 7. O-O (7. Nb5 Qd8 8. d5 Nb4 $14) 7... Nb4 (7... O-O-O $5
$11) 8. Nb5 Qb6 9. c3 Nc2 (9... c6 $5 10. cxb4 cxb5 $16) 10. Bf4 Nd5 11. Bg3 (
11. Nxc7+ Nxc7 12. Bxc7 Qxc7 13. Bb5+ Kd8 $16) 11... a6 (11... Nxa1 $142 $5 {
and Black hangs on} 12. Qxa1 c6 $15) 12. Nxc7+ $14 Nxc7 {Black wins a piece}
13. Rc1 e6 14. Bd3 Bxd3 15. Qxd3 Nxd4 16. Qxd4 (16. Ne5 Nd5 17. cxd4 Be7 $14)
16... Qxd4 $11 17. Nxd4 Nd5 18. Rfd1 Be7 19. c4 {White threatens to win
material: c4xd5} Nf6 20. c5 Ne4 21. b4 (21. c6 $5 bxc6 22. Nxc6 Nxg3 23. hxg3
$14) 21... Nxg3 $11 22. hxg3 {White has new doubled pawns: g2+g3} Bg5 (22...
O-O-O 23. Kf1 $11) 23. c6 (23. f4 Be7 $14) 23... bxc6 (23... O-O-O 24. f4 Bf6
25. cxb7+ Kxb7 26. Nb3 Rxd1+ 27. Rxd1 $15) 24. Rxc6 (24. f4 c5 25. Nb3 Be7 26.
Nxc5 Bxc5+ 27. Rxc5 Ke7 $11) 24... O-O 25. Rd6 (25. Nb3 $5 {is an interesting
idea} Rfc8 26. Rxc8+ Rxc8 27. Rd6 $11) 25... Be7 $15 {Black threatens to win
material: Be7xd6} 26. Rd7 Bxb4 27. Nc6 Bc5 28. Rc1 {White threatens to win
material: Rc1xc5} Ba3 {Black threatens to win material: Ba3xc1} 29. Rc3 {
White threatens to win material: Rc3xa3} Bb2 {Black threatens to win material:
Bb2xc3} 30. Rb3 {White threatens to win material: Rb3xb2} (30. Ne7+ Kh8 31.
Rcc7 Ba3 $11) 30... Bf6 $15 31. Ra3 g6 32. Na7 (32. g4 $5 $15 {should be
investigated more closely}) 32... Rfb8 $17 33. Rxa6 Rb1+ 34. Kh2 Rf1 35. f3 $4
{White crumbles in face of a dire situation} (35. Rb6 $142 Rxf2 36. a4 $17)
35... Rb8 $19 36. a4 (36. Rxf7 Rbb1 37. Kh3 $19) 36... Rbb1 37. Kh3 h5 38. g4
Rh1+ 39. Kg3 Be5+ (39... h4+ 40. Kf4 Rhe1 41. Rxe6 fxe6 42. Rg7+ Kxg7 43. Nc6
g5#) 40. Kf2 Bf4 (40... Bf4 41. Rxe6 fxe6 42. Rd8+ Kf7 43. Ke2 Rb2+ 44. Kd3
Rd1+ 45. Kc3 Be5+ 46. Rd4 Bxd4+ 47. Kc4 Bxa7 48. gxh5 Bd4 49. f4 Bf6 50. hxg6+
Ke7 51. g4 Rc1+ 52. Kd3 Rc3+ 53. Ke4 Re2#) (40... Rbe1 41. Rd8+ Kg7 42. g3 h4
43. Rg8+ Kxg8 44. gxh4 Rhf1+ 45. Kg2 Rg1+ 46. Kh3 Rh1+ 47. Kg2 Rh2#) 0-1

