{A40: Unusual replies to 1 d4} 1. c4 b6 2. d4 Bb7 3. Nc3 e6 4. e4 Bb4 5. Bd3
Ne7 (5... Nc6 6. Nf3 d6 7. Bd2 e5 8. d5 Bxc3 9. Bxc3 Nce7 10. b4 Bc8 11. c5 Nf6
12. a4 O-O 13. O-O Ng6 14. a5 bxc5 15. bxc5 Nf4 16. h3 N6h5 17. Bc2 Qf6 18. Kh2
Nxg2 19. Kxg2 Nf4+ 20. Kh1 {Ljubojevic,L (2571)-Speelman,J (2507) Leon 2011 1/
2-1/2 (47)}) 6. Nf3 O-O $146 (6... f5 7. exf5 Nxf5 8. Bxf5 exf5 9. O-O O-O 10.
Bf4 Bxc3 11. bxc3 h6 12. Re1 d6 13. d5 Nd7 14. Nd4 Nc5 15. Qh5 Qf6 16. Ne6 Nxe6
17. Rxe6 Qf7 18. Qh4 Rae8 19. Rae1 Rxe6 20. dxe6 Qg6 21. Bg3 {Erdos,B (2208)
-Gara,T (2375) Hungary 2011 0-1 (47)}) 7. O-O c6 {Covers b5+d5} (7... Bxc3 8.
bxc3 d6 9. e5 $14) 8. e5 {White gains space} h6 {Prevents intrusion on g5} 9.
Ne4 {Black has a cramped position} d5 {Black threatens to win material: d5xe4}
10. Ng3 (10. a3 dxe4 11. Bxe4 Bd6 12. exd6 Qxd6 $14) 10... dxc4 11. Bxc4 c5 12.
a3 {White threatens to win material: a3xb4} Ba5 13. Be3 Ba6 (13... Nd7 $5 $11 {
should be examined more closely}) 14. Bxa6 $16 Nxa6 15. Ne4 (15. Qe2 Nc7 $16)
15... Nf5 $14 16. dxc5 Nxe3 17. fxe3 Nxc5 $2 (17... Qxd1 $142 18. Raxd1 bxc5
$14) 18. Nd6 $18 b5 19. b4 Bb6 20. bxc5 Bxc5 21. Re1 Qb6 22. Qb3 a6 23. Ne4 Be7
24. Rad1 (24. a4 Rad8 $18) 24... Qa5 (24... Rfd8 $16) 25. Nd6 $18 Rab8 26. Nd4
Qb6 27. Nxe6 (27. Rc1 $142 {might be the shorter path} Bxd6 28. exd6 Qxd6 29.
Rc6 $18) 27... fxe6 $4 {terrible, but what else could Black do to save the
game?} (27... Bxd6 $142 28. Nxf8 Bxf8 $18) 28. Qxe6+ Kh8 29. Qxe7 Ra8 (29...
Kh7 {what else?} 30. Ne4 Qg6 31. Nf6+ Kh8 $18) 30. Nf7+ Kh7 (30... Kg8 31. Rd6
Qc5 32. Nxh6+ Kh8 $18) 31. Rd6 Qa5 32. Rf1 Rae8 33. Qd7 {[%cal Ye5e6] White
prepares the advance e6} (33. Rxh6+ gxh6 34. Qd6 Re6 35. Qxf8 Qd8 36. Qxd8 Re8
37. Qf6 a5 38. Qxh6+ Kg8 39. Qh8#) 33... Qxa3 34. Qf5+ (34. Rxh6+ gxh6 35. Qf5+
Kg7 36. Qf6+ Kh7 37. Qxh6+ Kg8 38. Qh8#) 34... Kg8 35. Qf4 (35. Nxh6+ Kh8 36.
Nf7+ Kg8 37. Qh5 Qxe3+ 38. Kh1 Qg1+ 39. Kxg1 Rxf7 40. Qxf7+ Kh7 41. Qg6+ Kg8
42. Rf7 a5 43. Qxg7#) 35... Qb3 (35... Qa4 36. Qf3 Qc4 37. Nxh6+ Kh8 38. Qxf8+
Rxf8 39. Rxf8+ Kh7 40. Nf7 g6 41. Ng5+ Kg7 42. Rff6 Qc1+ 43. Kf2 Qc2+ 44. Kf3
Kh6 45. Ne4 Kg7 46. Rxg6+ Kf7 47. Rdf6+ Ke8 48. Rg8+ Kd7 49. Rg7+ Ke8 50. Nd6+
Kd8 51. Rf8#) 36. e6 (36. Nxh6+ $142 {seems even better} Kh8 37. Qxf8+ Rxf8 38.
Rxf8+ Kh7 39. Nf5 $18) 36... Kh7 (36... a5 $18 {hoping against hope}) 37. Qe4+
Kg8 38. Nxh6+ $1 {final destruction} gxh6 (38... Kh8 {doesn't get the cat off
the tree} 39. Rxf8+ Rxf8 40. Nf7+ Kg8 41. Ng5 Rc8 42. Qh7+ Kf8 43. Qh8+ Ke7 44.
Rd7+ Kf6 45. Qxg7+ Kf5 46. Rf7+ Kg4 47. Nh7+ Kh4 48. Qg5#) 39. Rxf8+ Rxf8 40.
Qg6+ (40. e7 Qf7 41. Qg4+ Kh7 42. exf8=Q Qxf8 43. Rd7+ Kh8 44. Qg6 Qf1+ 45.
Kxf1 b4 46. Qg7#) 40... Kh8 41. Qxh6+ Kg8 42. Qg5+ Kh8 43. h3 Qb1+ (43... Qc2 {
cannot undo what has already been done} 44. Qh6+ Kg8 45. Rd7 Qf2+ 46. Kh2 Rf7
47. Qg5+ Kh7 48. e7 Qf6 49. e8=Q Qg6 50. Qxf7+ Qxf7 51. Rxf7+ Kh8 52. Qd8#) 44.
Kh2 Qe4 (44... Qh7 {doesn't change anything anymore} 45. e7 Re8 46. Rd4 b4 47.
Qf6+ Qg7 48. Rh4+ Kg8 49. Qe6+ Qf7 50. Rg4+ Kh8 51. Qxf7 a5 52. Rh4#) 45. e7
Rf7 (45... Re8 {does not help much} 46. Rh6+ Qh7 47. Qf6+ Kg8 48. Rg6+ Qxg6 49.
Qxg6+ Kh8 50. Qxe8+ Kg7 51. Qf8+ Kg6 52. e8=Q+ Kg5 53. Qf4#) 46. Rh6+ Rh7 47.
Qf6+ Kg8 48. Qf8# 1-0

