{C87: Closed Ruy Lopez: Steinitz-type lines after 6 Re1 d6} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6
3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. c3 Bd7 6. O-O Nf6 7. Re1 Be7 (7... b5 8. Bc2 Bg4 9. h3
Bh5 10. d3 Be7 11. Nbd2 O-O 12. Nf1 d5 13. Ng3 Bg6 14. exd5 Qxd5 15. Nh4 Rad8
16. Ngf5 Rfe8 17. Bg5 Bf8 18. Bxf6 gxf6 19. Qg4 Kh8 20. Re3 Qd7 21. Rd1 Ne7 22.
d4 {Gagunashvili,M (2570)-Paichadze,L (2480) Tbilisi 2012 1-0 (66)}) 8. d4 (8.
d3 O-O 9. Nbd2 Qe8 10. Nf1 Kh8 11. Ng3 Bd8 12. h3 Ne7 13. Bc2 Nfg8 14. d4 f6
15. Nh4 g6 16. a3 Qf7 17. b4 Be6 18. Rf1 Qg7 19. Bb3 Bxb3 20. Qxb3 Nc6 21. Nf3
Qf7 22. Qd1 Re8 {Markovic,M (2460)-Dmitrovic,T (2273) Pozarevac 2012 1-0 (54)})
8... b5 {Black threatens to win material: b5xa4} 9. Bb3 $146 (9. Bc2 O-O 10.
Nbd2 (10. d5 Na5 11. Nbd2 c5 12. dxc6 Nxc6 13. Nf1 Re8 14. Bg5 Ng4 15. Qd2 Na5
16. b3 Qc7 17. Bxe7 Rxe7 18. Rac1 Rc8 19. Red1 Nb7 20. Bb1 Qb6 21. h3 Nf6 22.
Ne3 h6 23. Nh4 g6 24. c4 b4 {Kovalevskaya,E (2486)-Obukhov,A (2444) Samara
2002 0-1 (74)}) 10... Ne8 11. Nf1 Bf6 12. h3 h5 13. Ne3 g6 14. Nd5 Bg7 15. a4
Rb8 16. axb5 axb5 17. Bg5 f6 18. Be3 b4 19. dxe5 fxe5 20. Bg5 Nf6 21. Ba4 Kh8
22. cxb4 Nxb4 23. Bxf6 Bxf6 {Barczay,L (2370)-Farkas,G (2315) Eger 1986 1/2-1/2
}) 9... O-O 10. Nbd2 Bg4 11. h3 Bh5 12. Nf1 (12. Bd5 Qd7 $14) 12... h6 {
Controls g5} (12... Bxf3 13. Qxf3 exd4 14. Qd3 $11) 13. Ng3 $14 Bg6 14. Nh4 {
White threatens to win material: Nh4xg6} Bh7 15. Nhf5 Na5 16. Nxe7+ Qxe7 {
White has the pair of bishops} 17. Bc2 Kh8 18. b3 {Secures c4} Nc6 19. a4 Rab8
(19... exd4 $5 20. cxd4 Rfe8 $16) 20. d5 $16 Nd8 21. axb5 axb5 22. Ba3 Nd7 (
22... Qd7 23. Qd3 $16) 23. Bb4 Nb7 24. Bd3 Ndc5 (24... Nbc5 $5 $16) 25. Bxb5 f5
26. Bxc5 $4 {forfeits the advantage} (26. exf5 $142 {White clearly has the
better chances} Qf7 27. Re3 $16) 26... Nxc5 $11 27. Bc4 f4 {This push gains
space} 28. Nf5 Bxf5 (28... Qf6 29. f3 h5 30. b4 $11) 29. exf5 $14 Rxf5 30. b4
Nd7 31. Ra7 {White threatens to win material: Ra7xc7} (31. Bd3 Rff8 $14) 31...
Nb6 (31... Nf6 32. Qa1 $11) 32. Bb5 (32. Bd3 Rff8 $16) 32... Rbf8 (32... e4 33.
Bc6 $11) 33. c4 (33. Bd3 $5 R5f6 34. Qf3 $16) 33... f3 34. g3 Rg5 (34... Rh5
$142 35. Re3 e4 $11) 35. Rf1 $4 {White is ruining his position} (35. Re3 $142
$14 {would keep White alive}) 35... e4 $17 36. c5 $4 {another step towards the
grave} (36. Qd4 $142 e3 37. Ra3 $17) 36... dxc5 (36... Nxd5 $142 $5 {and Black
can already relax} 37. Kh2 e3 38. Re1 dxc5 39. Qc1 cxb4 40. Qc6 $19) 37. d6
Qxd6 (37... Qe6 38. Qxf3 exf3 39. Bc6 Qxh3 40. Bxf3 Rxf3 41. Ra8+ Nxa8 42. Ra1
Kh7 43. Rxa8 Rgxg3+ 44. fxg3 Rf1#) 38. bxc5 $4 {sad, but how else could White
save the game?} (38. Qxd6 $142 cxd6 39. Rb7 $19) 38... Qxc5 (38... Rxg3+ 39.
fxg3 Qxg3+ 40. Kh1 Qg2#) 39. Qb1 (39. Kh2 {there is nothing better in the
position} Rh5 40. Bd7 Nxd7 41. Qxd7 Qxa7 42. Qe7 $19) 39... Rxg3+ 40. Kh2 Rg2+
41. Kh1 Qf5 (41... Qf5 42. Bd7 Nxd7 43. Rxc7 Qxh3#) (41... Qe5 42. Bd7 Qh2#)
0-1

