{D02: 1 d4 d5 2 Nf3 sidelines, including 2...Nf6 3 g3 and 2...Nf6 3 Bf4} 1. d4
d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. Nf3 Bf5 4. e3 a6 $146 {Prevents intrusion on b5} (4... Nbd7 5.
Ne5 (5. Be2 e6 6. O-O Be7 7. c4 c6 8. Qb3 Qb6 9. c5 Qxb3 10. axb3 Bxb1 11.
Rfxb1 O-O 12. h3 Ne4 13. b4 a6 14. Bd3 f5 15. Re1 h6 16. Ne5 Nxe5 17. Bxe5 Bh4
18. Re2 Bf6 19. Bh2 Ng5 {Abergel,T (2506)-Ribeiro,R (2183) Fourmies 2011 1-0 
(55)}) 5... h6 6. c4 e6 7. Nc3 Be7 8. h3 O-O 9. Be2 dxc4 10. Bxc4 c5 11. dxc5
Nxe5 12. Bxe5 Nd7 13. Bg3 Nxc5 14. O-O a6 15. Qxd8 Rfxd8 16. Rfd1 Nd3 17. Bxd3
Bxd3 18. Be5 b5 19. a3 {Kodinets,K (2409)-Fingerov,D (2350) chessassistantclub.
com INT 2004 1/2-1/2 (57)}) (4... h6 5. h3 e6 6. c4 dxc4 7. Bxc4 Bd6 8. Bxd6
cxd6 9. Qb3 Qa5+ 10. Nc3 Nbd7 11. O-O O-O 12. Rfe1 d5 13. Bb5 Rfd8 14. Rec1 Nb6
15. Ne5 a6 16. Be2 Nfd7 17. f4 Nxe5 18. fxe5 Rac8 19. a3 {Mufic,G (2301)
-Margitic,Z (2199) Sibenik 2008 1/2-1/2}) 5. Nbd2 e6 6. Nh4 Be7 (6... Bg4 7.
Nhf3 $11) 7. Nxf5 $14 exf5 {White has the pair of bishops} 8. Bd3 {White
threatens to win material: Bd3xf5} Nc6 (8... Qd7 9. c4 $14) 9. c3 (9. Bxf5 g6
10. Bd3 O-O $16) 9... O-O (9... Qd7 $5 $11 {has some apparent merit}) 10. Bxf5
$16 g6 11. Bd3 Nh5 12. Bg3 (12. Bh6 Re8 $16) 12... Re8 13. Nf3 Nxg3 14. hxg3 {
Opposite coloured bishops appeared} Bf6 15. Qb3 Na5 16. Qa4 Nc4 (16... c6 17.
O-O-O $16) 17. Bxc4 b5 (17... dxc4 $5 18. Qxc4 b5 $16) 18. Bxb5 $1 $18 {the end
} axb5 19. Qb3 (19. Qxb5 Re6 $18) 19... Be7 (19... Rb8 20. O-O $16) 20. Ne5 (
20. Qxb5 Rb8 21. Qe2 Rc8 $18) 20... Ra6 (20... Bf6 21. Nd3 $16) 21. f4 (21.
Qxb5 Qa8 $18) 21... c5 (21... f6 $142 $5 22. Nf3 Bf8 $16) 22. dxc5 $18 Bxc5 23.
Qxb5 Qc8 24. b4 {White threatens to win material: b4xc5} (24. O-O-O $142 Rxa2
25. Qd7 Qxd7 26. Nxd7 Bxe3+ 27. Kb1 $18) 24... Rb6 $4 (24... Bxe3 $142 {
would keep Black in the game} 25. Qd3 Bb6 $11) 25. Qd3 (25. Qxc5 $142 {and
White has prevailed} Qe6 26. Qc7 $18) 25... Be7 (25... Bf8 26. O-O $18) 26. O-O
Bf6 27. Qxd5 Re7 (27... Rbe6 28. c4 Bxe5 29. fxe5 Rd8 $18) 28. c4 (28. Rad1 $5
{makes it even easier for White} Bxe5 29. Qd8+ Qxd8 30. Rxd8+ Kg7 31. fxe5 Ra6
$18) 28... Qe8 $2 (28... Bxe5 $5 29. fxe5 Rxb4 $16) 29. Qc5 (29. b5 Bxe5 30.
fxe5 Rxe5 $18) 29... Rbe6 (29... Rbb7 30. Rfd1 $18) 30. Rae1 (30. Rad1 $142 $5
{keeps an even firmer grip} Bxe5 31. fxe5 Qb8 $18) 30... Bxe5 31. fxe5 Rxe5 32.
Qd4 (32. Qd6 Rd7 33. Qf6 Rxe3 34. Rxe3 Qxe3+ 35. Kh2 Qh6+ 36. Qh4 Qd2 $18)
32... Rd7 (32... Re4 33. Qc3 Rxe3 34. Rxe3 Rxe3 $16) 33. Qf4 $4 {hands over
the advantage to the opponent} (33. Qc3 Rde7 34. Rf3 Qa4 $18) 33... Rf5 $2 (
33... Re4 34. Qf3 Rxc4 $14) 34. Qh6 $4 {White loses the upper hand} (34. Qg4
$142 Rxf1+ 35. Rxf1 Qxe3+ 36. Kh2 $18) 34... Re7 $4 {releasing the pressure on
the opponent} (34... Rh5 35. Qf4 Rf5 $18) 35. Rxf5 $18 gxf5 36. Qg5+ Kh8 37.
Qf6+ Kg8 38. Qg5+ {Twofold repetition} Kh8 39. Kf2 (39. Qxf5 $5 {and White can
already relax} h6 40. b5 Kg8 41. Qg4+ Kf8 $18) 39... Re5 (39... Ra7 {doesn't
improve anything} 40. Re2 $18) 40. Rh1 (40. Rh1 f4 41. Qxf4 $18) 1-0

