{D15: Slav Defence: 4 Nc3 a6 and gambit lines after 4 Nc3 dxc4} 1. d4 d5 2. c4
c6 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nf3 a6 5. Nc3 b5 6. c5 Nbd7 7. a3 g6 8. Be2 $146 (8. b4 Bg7 9.
Bb2 (9. a4 Bb7 10. Bd3 O-O 11. O-O Ne8 12. e4 dxe4 13. Bxe4 Ndf6 14. Bc2 Nc7
15. Bd2 bxa4 16. Rxa4 Nb5 17. Ne2 Bc8 18. Ne5 Qc7 19. Bf4 Qb7 20. Qd2 Be6 21.
Rfa1 Rfd8 22. h3 Nd5 23. Bg3 f6 {Loetscher,R (2420)-Nuber,K (2265) Germany
2014 1/2-1/2 (48)}) 9... O-O (9... a5 10. Bd3 O-O 11. O-O Qc7 12. h3 Ne8 13.
Qe2 e5 14. Nxe5 Nxe5 15. dxe5 Bxe5 16. f4 Bg7 17. e4 axb4 18. axb4 Rxa1 19.
Bxa1 dxe4 20. Bxe4 Nf6 21. Qf3 Bd7 22. Bd3 Re8 23. f5 Bxf5 24. Bxf5 {Mah,K 
(2419)-Jirka,J (2396) England 2012 1/2-1/2 (59)}) 10. a4 Rb8 11. axb5 axb5 12.
h3 Qc7 13. Ra2 Ne4 14. Qa1 Nxc3 15. Bxc3 f6 16. h4 e5 17. dxe5 Nxe5 18. h5 Re8
19. Be2 Bf5 20. hxg6 Bxg6 21. Kf1 Re7 22. Bd4 Rf8 {Vallejo Pons,F (2674)
-Jakovenko,D (2671) Lugo 2006 1/2-1/2 (62)}) (8. Bd3 Bg7 9. O-O O-O 10. b4 Ne8
11. e4 dxe4 12. Bxe4 Bb7 13. Bg5 Ndf6 14. Bc2 Nc7 15. Bb3 h6 16. Bh4 Nfd5 17.
Nxd5 Nxd5 18. Re1 Re8 19. Ne5 g5 20. Bg3 e6 21. Qh5 Qf6 22. Ng4 Qxd4 {Schwarz,
D (2286)-Betko,L (2208) Slovakia 2011 0-1 (64)}) 8... Bg7 9. O-O O-O 10. b4 a5
{The thematic attack} 11. Rb1 Re8 12. Qc2 e5 13. dxe5 (13. a4 axb4 14. Rxb4 Qa5
$11) 13... Nxe5 $15 14. Nd4 {The knight likes it on d4} Qc7 15. f4 {White
threatens to win material: f4xe5} (15. a4 axb4 16. Rxb4 bxa4 17. Rxa4 Rxa4 18.
Nxa4 Neg4 $11) 15... Neg4 {[%cal Yf6e4,Yg4f6,Ye5g4] The knight intends
Ne5-g4-f6-e4. Black threatens to win material: Ng4xe3} 16. Rf3 axb4 17. axb4
Ne4 18. h3 (18. Bd3 Bd7 19. Nce2 Ra4 $15) 18... Ngf6 (18... Bxd4 $142 $5 19.
exd4 Nxc3 20. Qxc3 Rxe2 21. hxg4 Raa2 $17) 19. Bd2 Nxc3 20. Bxc3 Ne4 {A
comfortable square for the black knight} 21. Rbf1 f5 22. Bb2 Bd7 23. Bd3 Ra2
24. Qb3 {White threatens to win material: Qb3xa2} Qa7 25. Bxe4 (25. Bb1 Ra4 26.
Rd1 Re7 $11) 25... Rxe4 $15 {A classical outpost} 26. R3f2 Qa4 27. Qxa4 $2 (27.
Qc3 $142 $5 $15 {and White can hope to survive}) 27... Rxa4 $19 28. Re2 (28.
Nf3 Rxe3 29. Bxg7 Kxg7 $19) 28... Rxb4 29. Ra1 $4 {an oversight. But White was
lost anyway.} (29. Rd1 $19) 29... Bxd4 30. Ra8+ (30. Bxd4 {does not save the
day} Rbxd4 31. exd4 Rxe2 $19) 30... Be8 31. Bxd4 Rbxd4 32. Rea2 (32. exd4 {
is not much help} Rxe2 33. Kf1 Re4 $19) 32... Ra4 (32... Rxe3 {makes it even
easier for Black} 33. Kf2 Rde4 34. Rb8 $19) 33. Kf2 (33. R2xa4 {doesn't change
the outcome of the game} bxa4 34. Kf2 Kf7 $19) 33... Rxa2+ 34. Rxa2 Ra4 (34...
Ra4 35. Re2 Rc4 $19) 0-1

