Ne4 8. Nxe4 fxe4 9. Nd2 c5 10. Nxe4 h6 11. Bh4 cxd4 12. O-O Nc6 13. Bf3 dxe3
14. fxe3 Bxb2 15. Rb1 Be5 16. Bg3 Kh7 17. Bxe5 Nxe5 18. Be2 Rxf1+ 19. Bxf1 b6
20. Qd5 Bf5 21. Rb2 Rc8 22. Rf2 {Juer,J (2215)-Elci,P (2300) Sao Paulo 2014
0-1 (46)}) (7... c6 8. O-O (8. h3 Nbd7 9. Qc2 Ne4 10. Nxe4 fxe4 11. Nd2 d5 12.
cxd5 cxd5 13. O-O h6 14. Bh4 Nf6 15. Rac1 Qe8 16. Qb3 g5 17. Bg3 Kh8 18. Rc7 h5
19. f3 g4 20. hxg4 hxg4 21. fxe4 Nh5 22. Bh4 Rxf1+ {Dunnington,A (2435)
-Toulzac,P (2265) Toulouse 1994 1-0}) 8... Qe8 9. b4 e5 10. dxe5 dxe5 11. c5 h6
12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. Nd2 e4 14. Qb3+ Kg7 15. Rfd1 a5 16. Rab1 axb4 17. Qxb4 Na6
18. Bxa6 Rxa6 19. Nc4 Qe7 20. Nd6 Be6 21. a4 Rb8 22. Ne2 {Szmetan,J (2394)
-Blit,J (2306) Avellaneda 2007 1/2-1/2}) 8. d5 {White threatens to win
material: d5xc6} Ne5 9. O-O Nxf3+ 10. Bxf3 h6 {Black threatens to win material:
h6xg5} 11. Bh4 Bd7 12. h3 {Secures g4} Rb8 13. a4 a6 {Consolidates b5} 14. Qe2
Qe8 (14... g5 15. Bg3 $11) 15. a5 (15. Bg3 Nh7 $11) 15... e5 (15... g5 16. Bg3
$11) 16. dxe6 Bxe6 17. Qd3 (17. Bxf6 $5 Bxf6 18. Nd5 Bxd5 19. cxd5 $14) 17...
Qf7 18. b3 Nd7 19. Rad1 $4 (19. Qc2 $142 $11 {would bring relief}) 19... Ne5
$19 20. Qc2 (20. Qd2 Nxf3+ 21. gxf3 f4 22. exf4 Qxf4 23. Qxf4 Rxf4 $19) 20...
Nxf3+ 21. gxf3 f4 22. exf4 Bxh3 23. Rfe1 $2 (23. Nd5 Rbe8 24. Rfe1 $19) 23...
Qxf4 24. Qxg6 (24. Nd5 {is not the saving move} Qxh4 25. Ne7+ Kh7 26. Qxg6+ Kh8
$19) 24... Qxh4 25. Nd5 (25. Re4 {does not solve anything} Qg5+ 26. Qxg5 hxg5
$19) 25... Qg5+ (25... Rxf3 $142 {might be the shorter path} 26. Re2 $19) 26.
Qxg5 hxg5 27. Re3 (27. Nxc7 {hardly improves anything} Rxf3 28. Rxd6 Kf7 $19)
27... Rf7 28. f4 (28. Ne7+ {cannot change destiny} Kh7 $19) 28... Bg4 29. Rde1
gxf4 30. Ne7+ (30. Re7 {a last effort to resist the inevitable} c6 31. Rxf7
Kxf7 32. Re7+ Kf8 33. Re4 $19) 30... Kh7 31. Re4 Be5 32. Nd5 (32. f3 {does not
win a prize} Bxf3 33. Rxe5 dxe5 34. Rxe5 Re8 $19) 32... Bf3 33. Rxe5 dxe5 34.
Rxe5 (34. Rc1 $19 {the only chance to get some counterplay}) 34... Kg6 35. Re6+
Kf5 36. Rh6 Re8 37. Kf1 c6 38. Nc3 Rg7 (38... Rfe7 39. Rh5+ Kg4 40. Rh4+ Kxh4
41. Ne2 Rxe2 42. Kg1 Re1+ 43. Kh2 Rh1#) 39. Rh2 (39. Rh5+ {cannot change what
is in store for ?} Kf6 40. Nd5+ cxd5 41. Rh6+ Kf7 42. Re6 Rxe6 43. cxd5 Bg2+
44. Kg1 Re1+ 45. Kh2 Rh1#) 39... Rge7 (39... Rge7 40. Ne2 Rxe2 41. Rh5+ Kg6 42.
Rg5+ Kxg5 43. Kg1 Re1+ 44. Kh2 Rh1#) (39... Rg1+ 40. Kxg1 Re1#) 0-1

